other_tests.findings: Lower Thorax: Minimal linear atelectasis in the lung bases. No pleural effusion. Liver: Homogeneous parenchyma with no focal abnormalities. Gallbladder distended with calculi, no pericholecystic fluid or wall thickening. Common duct normal at 4 mm. Kidneys: Mild right hydronephrosis, proximal hydroureter likely due to compression by gravid uterus. Appendix: Retrocecal position, dilated to 11 mm with fat stranding and prominent lymph nodes, possible appendicoliths. Cecal wall thickened and edematous, no abscess. Prominent lymph nodes (6 mm short axis) medial to inflamed appendix. Single intrauterine gestation visible, normal appearance of ovaries.
